exceptions.exn: In environment n, m : nat H : (fix eqb (n m : nat) {struct n} : bool := match n with | 0 => match m with | 0 => true | S _ => false end | S n' => match m with | 0 => false | S m' => eqb n' m' end end) n m = true The term "H" has type "(fix eqb (n m : nat) {struct n} : bool := match n with | 0 => match m with | 0 => true | S _ => false end | S n' => match m with | 0 => false | S m' => eqb n' m' end end) n m = true" while it is expected to have type "(?n =? ?n')%N = true".

original: intros n m H. unfold Nat.eqb in H. destruct n, m. - reflexivity. - discriminate. - discriminate. - f_equal. apply (Neqb_complete _ _ H).
